   "author_association" : "MEMBER",
   "body" : "If I interrupt CWallet::AddToWallet at the start, while it is adding a new coinbase transaction (or probably any first-seen-in-block) - for example with \"quit\" in GDB or SIGKILL - after restarting, Bitcoin-Qt (and bitcoind?) will not pick up on this transaction even after completely catching up. -rescan is then needed to see it.\n",
